parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Electrical Failure and Sensor System Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent electrical failure and sensor system malfunctions can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, display faulty warning lights, and affect the functionality of various safety features, such as automatic emergency braking and collision detection. This can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
warning lights on the dash appear and disappear
the malfunction light and car collision lights come on
the vehicle struggles to stay running
the backup camera display goes dark
and the slip indicator light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning AEB system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The faulty system can also cause warning lights to appear on the dash, distracting the driver and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The AEB system warning light appears on the dash
the front radar obstruction warning message appears
and the blind spot warning lights appear randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Gauge Indicator and Approximate Mileage Data Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel gauge indicator and approximate mileage data can cause driver disinformation, leading to the possibility of running out of fuel on the highway, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The fuel gauge indicator displays incorrect information
the approximate mileage data is inaccurate
and the fuel gauge indicator bar does not increase after refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to stall, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the AEB system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or slow down without reason, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on high-speed roads.

false warnings and readings on the dashboard
sudden loss of speed or braking without reason.
